                          h3.lightblue Melanie Mediavilla-Varela, Ph.D., Director of Research                   
                    .row.nomargin
                        .col-md-2
                                img(src='/images/Melanie.jpg' class='maxwidth')
                        .col-xs-12.col-md-8                                                          
                             .bio Dr. Mediavilla-Varela holds a Ph.D. in microbiology and molecular genetics from Loma Linda University in California. At Nilogen, she applies her vast knowledge of cancer immunology and biology to its technology platforms specializing in the following immunological techniques: allogeneic assays, flow cytometric analysis of cytokines, ELISpot analysis of cytokines, ELISA assays, and qRT-PCR. Before joining Nilogen, Dr. Mediavilla-Varela worked as a postdoctoral fellow at the H. Lee Moffitt Cancer Center in Tampa and as a research assistant at the University of Puerto Rico, School of Medicine. In addition to her work in the sciences, she obtained a business certificate from the University of South Florida in Tampa.  
